{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17413230","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17413230"},"attributes":{"position":12,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T08:02:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T08:02:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2605"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17507135","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17507135"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:50:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:50:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2605"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"2605","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2605"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.06,0.41,0.29,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2605"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50499"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2605","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2605"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2605"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35716"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1040"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2805"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6364"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7752"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38412"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/50499"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 57-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner with a two week history of constant, dull left-sided abdominal pain. She is otherwise well and does not have any gastrointestinal nor genito-urinary symptoms. Her medical history includes a colonic resection for carcinoma three years previously and her follow-up investigations performed six months ago were normal. On examination her blood pressure is 124/76 mmHg, pulse 84/min and temperature 37.3C. Nothing abnormal is found on abdominal examination. A CT scan is arranged and a representative slice is shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mesenteric cyst","Pancreatic pseudocyst","Hydronephrosis","Splenic cyst","Pseudo-obstruction"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT scan shows a multi-component cystic structure in the left side of the abdominal cavity (Image). This is a portal venous phase film and the right kidney is clearly defined. This cystic structure on the left shows thin rims of renal parenchyma. This patient has gross left-sided \u003Cstrong\u003Ehydronephrosis. \u003C/strong\u003EFurther examination of the other CT slices showed that the hydronephrosis was secondary to obstruction of the ureter by a tumour deposit from the previously treated colonic cancer. There is little functioning parenchymal tissue left - a rim of contrast-enhancing renal tissue can be seen surrounding the dilated pelvi-calyceal system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMesenteric cyst\u003C/strong\u003E is an umbrella term that encompasses any type of cyst arising in the mesentery. They are rare and are usually intimately associated with bowel loops.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA\u003Cstrong\u003E pancreatic pseudocyst\u003C/strong\u003E is a well recognised complication of acute pancreatitis. These pseudocysts are often found during the follow-up imaging of pancreatitis, and can be asymptomatic unless they have started to compress on adjacent structures. On imaging, they appear as fluid-filled oval or round collections with a relatively thick wall, and are most commonly situated in the pancreatic bed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESplenic cyst\u003C/strong\u003E can be subdivided into primary or secondary cysts (secondary to trauma or infarction). Imaging typically shows a hypoattenuating, well-defined lesion with sharp demarcation to the splenic parenchyma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPseudo-obstruction\u003C/strong\u003E, also known as Ogilvie syndrome, describes the dilatation of colon without mechanical obstruction. Patients usually present with constipation, nausea \u0026amp; vomiting and abdominal distension while imaging reveals gross dilatation of large bowel without evidence of an abrupt transition point.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Tumour extension from adjacent organs into the ureter can result in urinary obstruction and subsequently, hydronephrosis."],"references":["Yacoub JH, Clark JA, Paal EE, Manning MA. Approach to Cystic Lesions in the Abdomen and Pelvis, with Radiologic-Pathologic Correlation. RadioGraphics [Internet]. 2021 Sep [cited 2022 Nov 29];41(5):1368-86. Available from: https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2021200207"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35716"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2605"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18436"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20915"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18436","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18436"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ae2eaf76-95f2-4e04-9333-2dcd113595cb.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ae2eaf76-95f2-4e04-9333-2dcd113595cb.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":524,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"20915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20915"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/To703igYiFKuI0rlnPZCBipTbLeH3m.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/To703igYiFKuI0rlnPZCBipTbLeH3m.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":567,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35716","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/35716"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-08-12T16:05:10+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-23T20:12:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2605"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50499"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"36","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/36"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relatio